"{\"uid\": \"cruxnow.com-church-in-europe-2024-07-bishops-around-the-world-blast-last-supper-parody-at-paris-olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Drag queens perform during the Opening Ceremony of the Paris Olympics, on July 26, 2024.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 94, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6, \"end\": 17, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drag_queen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Drag queens\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drag_queen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drag_queen\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Opening Ceremony\", \"from\": 27, \"to\": 47}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 51, \"to\": 69}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 74, \"to\": 78}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Credit: @OlympicsParis/X, The Olympic Games/X.)\", \"from\": 95, \"to\": 143, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"(Credit\", \"from\": 95, \"to\": 102}, {\"ngram\": \"@OlympicsParis/X\", \"from\": 104, \"to\": 120}, {\"ngram\": \"The Olympic Games\", \"from\": 122, \"to\": 139}, {\"ngram\": \"X.\", \"from\": 140, \"to\": 142}]}, {\"sentence\": \"BOSTON - After the opening ceremony of the Paris Olympic Games inspired shock and drew sharp criticism over an apparent drag parody of the Last Supper, Catholic leaders in France and around the world have condemned the incident.\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 297, \"end\": 305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0623856709914675e-15, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 317, \"end\": 323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9796816040502914, \"rank\": 0.018573198923477585, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"BOSTON\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 151}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 160, \"to\": 180}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympic Games\", \"from\": 184, \"to\": 207}, {\"ngram\": \"shock\", \"from\": 217, \"to\": 222}, {\"ngram\": \"sharp criticism\", \"from\": 232, \"to\": 247}, {\"ngram\": \"an apparent drag parody\", \"from\": 253, \"to\": 276}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 295}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 335, \"to\": 344}, {\"ngram\": \"the incident\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 372}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The values and the principles expressed and disseminated by sport and Olympism contribute to this need for unity and fraternity that our world needs so much, respecting the convictions of all, around the sport that brings us together and in order to promote peace among nations and hearts,\\\" the French bishops said in a July 27 statement.\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 671, \"end\": 677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9998226960401994, \"rank\": 0.00017733281995343158, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The values\", \"from\": 376, \"to\": 386}, {\"ngram\": \"the principles\", \"from\": 391, \"to\": 405}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 441}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympism\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 454}, {\"ngram\": \"this need\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 478}, {\"ngram\": \"unity\", \"from\": 483, \"to\": 488}, {\"ngram\": \"our world\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 518}, {\"ngram\": \"the convictions\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 560}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 585}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 600}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 617, \"to\": 622}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 639}, {\"ngram\": \"nations\", \"from\": 646, \"to\": 653}, {\"ngram\": \"hearts\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 664}, {\"ngram\": \"a July 27 statement\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 713}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony organized by the Organizing Committee for the Olympic and Paralympic Games (COJOP), they said, \\\"offered the whole world wonderful moments of beauty and joy, rich in emotions and universally acclaimed.\\\"\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 795, \"end\": 811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999685219341, \"rank\": 2.906784421027285e-08, \"text\": \"Paralympic Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opening ceremony\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"the Organizing Committee\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 774}, {\"ngram\": \"COJOP\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole world\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 856}, {\"ngram\": \"wonderful moments\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"beauty\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 884}, {\"ngram\": \"joy\", \"from\": 889, \"to\": 892}, {\"ngram\": \"emotions\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 910}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, they noted that the ceremony also \\\"unfortunately included scenes of derision and mockery of Christianity, which we deeply deplore.\\\"\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 1080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1041, \"end\": 1053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9992702063439622, \"rank\": 0.0007303266194768164, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 965, \"to\": 977}, {\"ngram\": \"scenes\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1013}, {\"ngram\": \"derision\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1025}, {\"ngram\": \"mockery\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1037}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The July 26 opening Olympic opening ceremony featured a fashion show with men in drag making suggestive runway walks, and included what appeared to a mockery of the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1259, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The July\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1090}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1126}, {\"ngram\": \"a fashion show\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1150}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1159}, {\"ngram\": \"drag making suggestive runway walks\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1198}, {\"ngram\": \"a mockery\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1239}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1258}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At one point during the ceremony, a group of 18 drag performers, including several famous Drag Race France personalities, struck poses behind what appeared to be a long table with the Seine River and Eiffel Tower in the background.\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1351, \"end\": 1367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drag_Race_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Drag Race France\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drag_Race_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drag_Race_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one point\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1273}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1293}, {\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1302}, {\"ngram\": \"18 drag performers\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1324}, {\"ngram\": \"poses\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1395}, {\"ngram\": \"a long table\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1435}, {\"ngram\": \"the Seine River\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1456}, {\"ngram\": \"Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1473}, {\"ngram\": \"the background\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1491}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the center was a woman in a low-cut dress wearing a large silver headdress, reminiscent of the halo behind Jesus's head in many artistic depictions of the Last Supper, indicating his divine status as the son of God.\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1604, \"end\": 1609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999988663149, \"rank\": 1.1338120910684219e-09, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the center\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1507}, {\"ngram\": \"a woman\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1519}, {\"ngram\": \"a low-cut dress\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1538}, {\"ngram\": \"the halo\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1596}, {\"ngram\": \"many artistic depictions\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1644}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1663}, {\"ngram\": \"his divine status\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"the son\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1704}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1711}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The woman made a heart shape with her hands as the group stared into the camera before breaking out into a routine.\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1828, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The woman\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1722}, {\"ngram\": \"a heart shape\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1741}, {\"ngram\": \"her hands\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1756}, {\"ngram\": \"the group\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1769}, {\"ngram\": \"the camera\", \"from\": 1782, \"to\": 1792}, {\"ngram\": \"a routine\", \"from\": 1818, \"to\": 1827}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As models then took the stage for an impromptu fashion show, the Last Supper characters swayed on the sidelines as a little girl stood with them.\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1975, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"models\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"the stage\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1859}, {\"ngram\": \"an impromptu fashion show\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1889}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper characters\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 1917}, {\"ngram\": \"the sidelines\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 1941}, {\"ngram\": \"a little girl\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 1958}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Later, a large serving tray was placed on the stage, with the top being removed to reveal a scantily clad man painted head to toe in blue, apparently evoking the Greek God Dionysus in a bid to point to the \\\"absurdity of violence between human beings,\\\" according to the official English-language Olympic Games profile on social media platform X, previously known as Twitter.\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 2350, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2139, \"end\": 2144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.8649338373527842, \"rank\": 0.09089642452080472, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2149, \"end\": 2157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5232687330115388e-28, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 2342, \"end\": 2349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1441483889445222e-21, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a large serving tray\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 2004}, {\"ngram\": \"the stage\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2028}, {\"ngram\": \"a scantily clad man\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2086}, {\"ngram\": \"head\", \"from\": 2095, \"to\": 2099}, {\"ngram\": \"toe\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2106}, {\"ngram\": \"a bid\", \"from\": 2161, \"to\": 2166}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"absurdity\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2193}, {\"ngram\": \"violence\", \"from\": 2197, \"to\": 2205}, {\"ngram\": \"human beings\", \"from\": 2214, \"to\": 2226}, {\"ngram\": \"the official English-language Olympic Games profile\", \"from\": 2242, \"to\": 2293}, {\"ngram\": \"social media platform X\", \"from\": 2297, \"to\": 2320}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers came under fire for the spectacle, with critics condemning not only the provocative nature of the drag show and the apparent mockery of Christianity, but also for the presence of a child at the table alongside the men in drag.\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2589, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2499, \"end\": 2511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9992702063439622, \"rank\": 0.0007303266194768164, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2362}, {\"ngram\": \"fire\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2378}, {\"ngram\": \"the spectacle\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2396}, {\"ngram\": \"critics\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2410}, {\"ngram\": \"not only the provocative nature\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2453}, {\"ngram\": \"the drag show\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2470}, {\"ngram\": \"the apparent mockery\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2495}, {\"ngram\": \"the presence\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2538}, {\"ngram\": \"a child\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2549}, {\"ngram\": \"the table\", \"from\": 2553, \"to\": 2562}, {\"ngram\": \"the men\", \"from\": 2573, \"to\": 2580}, {\"ngram\": \"drag\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2588}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some commentators have claimed that the performance was evocative of the feast of Dionysus, rather than the Last Supper, as a nod to the Greek roots of the Olympic games.\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2761, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2673, \"end\": 2681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5232687330115388e-28, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 2728, \"end\": 2733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.8649338373527842, \"rank\": 0.09089642452080472, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some commentators\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2608}, {\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 2627, \"to\": 2642}, {\"ngram\": \"the feast\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2669}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 2695, \"to\": 2710}, {\"ngram\": \"a nod\", \"from\": 2715, \"to\": 2720}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic games\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2760}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the vast majority have associated it with the Last Supper, as the layout was reminiscent of artist Leonardo Da Vinci's famed painting.\", \"from\": 2762, \"to\": 2905, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2817, \"end\": 2828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.086126449418227e-38, \"text\": \"Last Supper\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\"}, {\"begin\": 2870, \"end\": 2878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1950066391631612e-25, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 2879, \"end\": 2887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.465439435519753e-35, \"text\": \"Da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the vast majority\", \"from\": 2771, \"to\": 2788}, {\"ngram\": \"the layout\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2843}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French member of parliament Marion Mar\\u00e9chal, a practicing Catholic, wrote on X, \\\"To all the Christians of the world who are watching the #Paris2024 ceremony and felt insulted by this drag queen parody of the Last Supper, know that it is not France that is speaking but a left-wing minority ready for any provocation.\\\"\", \"from\": 2907, \"to\": 3224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2907, \"end\": 2913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9998226960401994, \"rank\": 0.00017733281995343158, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2935, \"end\": 2950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marion_Mar\\u00e9chal\", \"score\": 0.9999998162447978, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marion Mar\\u00e9chal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marion_Mar\\u00e9chal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marion_Mar\\u00e9chal\"}, {\"begin\": 2965, \"end\": 2973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0623856709914675e-15, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 2999, \"end\": 3009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9921992567180183, \"rank\": 0.006643844996118731, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 3148, \"end\": 3154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9796816040502914, \"rank\": 0.018573198923477585, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"X\", \"from\": 2984, \"to\": 2985}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3013, \"to\": 3022}, {\"ngram\": \"the #Paris2024 ceremony\", \"from\": 3040, \"to\": 3063}, {\"ngram\": \"this drag queen parody\", \"from\": 3085, \"to\": 3107}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 3111, \"to\": 3126}, {\"ngram\": \"a left-wing minority\", \"from\": 3176, \"to\": 3196}, {\"ngram\": \"any provocation\", \"from\": 3207, \"to\": 3222}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Italian Archbishop Vincenzo Paglia, president of the Vatican's Pontifical Academy for Life, wrote on X that \\\"the derision and the mockery of the Last Supper\\\" at the Paris Olympics, which he said was \\\"rightly deplored\\\" by the French bishops, \\\"reveals a profound question.\\\"\", \"from\": 3226, \"to\": 3497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3226, \"end\": 3233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9999930670655198, \"rank\": 6.676406831389104e-06, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3245, \"end\": 3260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincenzo_Paglia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vincenzo Paglia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincenzo_Paglia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincenzo_Paglia\"}, {\"begin\": 3451, \"end\": 3457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9998226960401994, \"rank\": 0.00017733281995343158, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 3262, \"to\": 3271}, {\"ngram\": \"the Vatican's Pontifical Academy\", \"from\": 3275, \"to\": 3307}, {\"ngram\": \"Life\", \"from\": 3312, \"to\": 3316}, {\"ngram\": \"X\", \"from\": 3327, \"to\": 3328}, {\"ngram\": \"the derision\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3347}, {\"ngram\": \"the mockery\", \"from\": 3352, \"to\": 3363}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 3367, \"to\": 3382}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 3387, \"to\": 3405}, {\"ngram\": \"a profound question\", \"from\": 3476, \"to\": 3495}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everyone, absolutely everyone, wants to sit at the table where Jesus gives his life for all and teaches love,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3499, \"to\": 3619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3563, \"end\": 3568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999988663149, \"rank\": 1.1338120910684219e-09, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Everyone\", \"from\": 3500, \"to\": 3508}, {\"ngram\": \"absolutely everyone\", \"from\": 3510, \"to\": 3529}, {\"ngram\": \"the table\", \"from\": 3547, \"to\": 3556}, {\"ngram\": \"his life\", \"from\": 3575, \"to\": 3583}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 3604, \"to\": 3608}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maltese Archbishop Charles Scicluna, who serves as archbishop of Malta and as adjunct secretary of the disciplinary section of the Vatican's Dicastery for the Doctrine of the Faith, lodged a formal complaint with the French ambassador to Malta, and has urged others to do the same.\", \"from\": 3621, \"to\": 3902, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3629, \"end\": 3639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9718539604957414, \"rank\": 0.028563644533177477, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 3640, \"end\": 3656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charles Scicluna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\"}, {\"begin\": 3686, \"end\": 3691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"score\": 0.9999999994579412, \"rank\": 5.421137050641315e-10, \"text\": \"Malta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\"}, {\"begin\": 3838, \"end\": 3844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9998226960401994, \"rank\": 0.00017733281995343158, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3859, \"end\": 3864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"score\": 0.9999999994579412, \"rank\": 5.421137050641315e-10, \"text\": \"Malta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"archbishop\", \"from\": 3672, \"to\": 3682}, {\"ngram\": \"adjunct secretary\", \"from\": 3699, \"to\": 3716}, {\"ngram\": \"the disciplinary section\", \"from\": 3720, \"to\": 3744}, {\"ngram\": \"the Vatican's Dicastery\", \"from\": 3748, \"to\": 3771}, {\"ngram\": \"the Doctrine\", \"from\": 3776, \"to\": 3788}, {\"ngram\": \"the Faith\", \"from\": 3792, \"to\": 3801}, {\"ngram\": \"a formal complaint\", \"from\": 3810, \"to\": 3828}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 3880, \"to\": 3886}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In his complaint, which he published on social media, Scicluna said, \\\"I would like to express my distress and great disappointment at the insult to us Christians during the opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympics when a group of drag artists parodied the Last Supper of Jesus.\\\"\", \"from\": 3904, \"to\": 4185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4055, \"end\": 4065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9921992567180183, \"rank\": 0.006643844996118731, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his complaint\", \"from\": 3907, \"to\": 3920}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 3944, \"to\": 3956}, {\"ngram\": \"Scicluna\", \"from\": 3958, \"to\": 3966}, {\"ngram\": \"my distress\", \"from\": 3998, \"to\": 4009}, {\"ngram\": \"great disappointment\", \"from\": 4014, \"to\": 4034}, {\"ngram\": \"the insult\", \"from\": 4038, \"to\": 4048}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 4073, \"to\": 4093}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 4097, \"to\": 4120}, {\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 4126, \"to\": 4133}, {\"ngram\": \"drag artists\", \"from\": 4137, \"to\": 4149}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 4159, \"to\": 4174}, {\"ngram\": \"Jesus\", \"from\": 4178, \"to\": 4183}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bishop Andrew Cozzens of Crookston, Minnesota, who serves as Chairman of the Board of the National Eucharistic Congress and who in that capacity recently presided over the event in Indianapolis, which drew some 50,000 people, sent a response to all congress participants about the Olympic performance.\", \"from\": 4187, \"to\": 4488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4187, \"end\": 4208, \"title\": \"http://dbp